  "title": "documentation: webpage performance",
  "body": "After we release 1.0.0, we can optimize again the documentation (by order of importance):\n- [ ] use an svg sprite (can be generated on https://icomoon.io/) =>  -- requests for small things\n  There are also gulp/grunt tasks to automate this I believe. Like https://github.com/jkphl/svg-sprite\n- [x] use minified versions for JS and CSS (currently using unminified main.css, home.js, default-theme.css)\n- [x] combine jquery plugins from jsdelivr in a single jsdelivr tag => -- requests for small things\n- [ ] optimize svg sprite in the build step (svgo sprite.png)\n- [ ] optimize remaining img on build\n- [ ] minify html\n  Any other idea, add it here\n",
